00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:27,120
Example two.
例子二。

194
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,840
Be sure not to forget your umbrella.
确保不要忘记带伞。

195
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:33,280
It's raining today.
今天下雨。

196
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:36,280
Example three.
例子三。

197
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:43,720
I told him to be sure not to do anything stupid, but he did.
我告诉他确保不要做任何蠢事，但他还是做了。

198
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:48,760
So Marco, why should we say be sure not to instead of don't?
那么Marco，为什么我们要说“确保不要”而不是“不要”？

199
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:51,640
I think don't sounds more like an order.
我觉得“不要”听起来更像命令。

200
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,640
Okay.
好的。

201
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:53,640
Very direct.
非常直接。

202
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:57,420
Maybe be sure not to is a little bit softer, a little bit more friendly.
也许“be sure not to”稍微柔和一点，更友好一些。

203
00:07:57,420 --> 00:07:58,960
So be sure not to.
所以是“be sure not to”。

204
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,920
Now for our last phrase.
现在来看我们最后一个短语。

205
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:06,640
So the pharmacist in the end wanted to check for the price and he said, just hang on there
所以药剂师最后想查一下价格，他说，“just hang on there”

206
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,900
a sec.
a sec。

207
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:09,280
So that's interesting.
这挺有意思的。

208
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:10,280
Hang on.
Hang on。

209
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,280
Hang on.
Hang on。

210
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,280
Hang on.
Hang on。

211
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,280
Well, hang on.
嗯，Hang on。

212
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:14,480
What does he mean by hang on?
他说的“hang on”是什么意思？

213
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,480
He means wait.
他的意思是“等一等”。

214
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,480
Wait.
等一等。

215
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,120
It's an informal way of saying wait.
这是“等一等”的非正式说法。

216
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,120
Exactly.
没错。

217
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,760
It's also a little bit more friendly than just saying wait.
它也比直接说“等一等”更友好一些。

218
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,760
Right.
对。

219
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:23,760
Exactly.
没错。

220
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,760
And we can change the time a little bit, right?
我们还可以稍微改变一下时间长度，对吧？

221
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,760
Yeah.
是的。

222
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:28,920
So we can say hang on a second.
所以我们可以说“hang on a second”。

223
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,480
Or hang on a moment.
或者“hang on a moment”。

224
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,480
Hang on a minute.
“Hang on a minute”。

225
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,480
All right.
好的。

226
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,480
What about hang on an hour?
那“hang on an hour”呢？

227
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:37,080
Well, maybe if you're telling someone to wait for an hour, just hang on there for an hour.
嗯，如果你要告诉别人等一个小时，可以说“just hang on there for an hour”。

228
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,080
I'll be there soon.
我很快就到。

229
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,080
Yeah.
是的。

230
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,320
But I guess it's more common hang on a minute.
但我觉得更常见的是“hang on a minute”。

231
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,320
Right.
对。

232
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,680
Maybe for shorter periods of time.
可能用于较短的时间。

233
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:43,680
Okay.
好的。

234
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:47,360
So with these phrases, I think now we can use them in different circumstances, obviously
所以有了这些短语，我想我们现在可以在不同场合使用它们了，显然

235
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:50,360
not only in the pharmacy.
不仅仅是在药房里。

236
00:08:50,360 --> 00:09:00,760
But let's listen to our dialogue for the last time.
但让我们最后听一遍对话。

237
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,760
Hello sir.
你好，先生。

238
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:02,760
How can I help you?
有什么能帮您的？

239
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:03,760
Yes.
是的。

240
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:06,320
I need this prescription, please.
我需要这张处方，谢谢。

241
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,320
Let's see.
让我看看。

242
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,320
Okay.
好的。

243
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:10,520
So 50 milligrams of Prozac.
所以是50毫克的百忧解。

244
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:13,040
Would you prefer this in capsule or tablet?
您想要胶囊还是片剂？

245
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,440
Capsules are fine.
胶囊就行。

246
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,440
Okay.
好的。

247
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,640
You should take one capsule three times a day.
您应该每天服用三次，每次一粒胶囊。

248
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:22,400
Be sure not to take it on an empty stomach and also don't ever mix it with alcohol.
切记不要空腹服用，也千万不要和酒精一起服用。

249
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,120
Yes, I know.
是的，我知道。

250
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,760
It's not the first time I'm taking this.
这不是我第一次吃这个药了。

251
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:26,760
Don't worry.
别担心。

252
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:27,760
I won't overdose.
我不会过量服用的。

253
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:28,920
Okay.
好的。

254
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,400
Anything else I can get you?
还需要别的吗？

255
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,840
Oh, yes.
哦，是的。

256
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,840
I almost forgot.
我差点忘了。

257
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:36,880
Can I also get some eye drops and some condoms?
能再给我一些眼药水和避孕套吗？

258
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:37,880
Sure.
当然。

259
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:41,280
Darn, condoms aren't registered in our system.
糟糕，避孕套没有录入我们的系统。

260
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,600
Oh, well, that's okay.
哦，那没关系。

261
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,600
I'll get some later.
我晚点再买。

262
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,600
Thanks.
谢谢。

263
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,800
Really, it's no problem.
真的，没问题。

264
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:49,080
Just hang on there a sec.
请稍等一下。

265
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:56,200
Can I get a price check on Funtimes Ribbed Condoms, please?
能帮我查一下Funtimes螺纹避孕套的价格吗？

266
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:58,800
Okay.
好的。

267
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:02,400
So with medicine, an interesting thing comes up, right?
所以关于药物，有一个有趣的地方，对吧？

268
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,400
That's right.
没错。

269
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,760
A lot of people think that you eat medicine.
很多人认为“吃”药。

270
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,760
Okay.
好的。

271
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,760
Or drink medicine?
或者“喝”药？

272
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:08,760
Yeah.
是的。

273
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:10,920
But in English, you always take medicine.
但在英语中，你总是“take medicine”。

274
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:11,920
Always take medicine.
总是“take medicine”。

275
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:12,920
Yeah.
是的。

276
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,880
So you never can say, oh, I ate my medicine yesterday.
所以你永远不能说，“哦，我昨天吃了药”。

277
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:17,200
It always has to be, I took my medicine.
必须说，“我服了药”。

278
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,200
Okay.
好的。

279
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,200
So you take the capsules.
所以是“take the capsules”。

280
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,200
Exactly.
没错。

281
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,200
Or take the tablets.
或者“take the tablets”。

282
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,200
All right.
好的。

283
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,200
So you take medicine.
所以是“take medicine”。

284
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:27,040
Now, an interesting thing in the United States, for example, it's very hard to get medicine
现在，在美国有一个有趣的现象，比如，很难

285
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,960
without a prescription.
在没有处方的情况下买到药。

286
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:29,960
That's right.
没错。

287
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:35,680
So we always talk about prescription medicine and OTC medicine or over-the-counter medicine.
所以我们经常谈论处方药和非处方药（OTC）。

288
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:37,680
So over-the-counter medicine is?
那么非处方药是？

289
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:41,760
Is medicine you can just buy without that prescription or note from your doctor.
就是不需要医生处方或证明就能直接买的药。

290
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:42,760
Okay.
好的。

291
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:46,760
So for example, if you have a headache, you can go to the pharmacy and buy aspirin.
比如，如果你头疼，可以去药房买阿司匹林。

292
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,760
Yeah.
是的。

293
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:49,640
And that's over-the-counter medicine.
那就是非处方药。

294
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:53,160
But prescription medicine, you can't get it without the doctor's note.
但处方药，没有医生的证明就拿不到。

295
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:54,160
Yes.
是的。

296
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:57,080
And like you said, in America, you almost have to have a prescription for everything.
就像你说的，在美国，几乎什么都要处方。

297
00:10:57,080 --> 00:11:01,360
Which is strange because people can overdose on aspirin.
这很奇怪，因为人们可能会过量服用阿司匹林。

298
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:05,740
So tell us how medicine and pharmacies work in your countries.
所以请告诉我们，在你们国家，药物和药房是怎么运作的。

299
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:10,800
And also if you have questions or comments, our website, EnglishPod.com is always open
另外，如果你有问题或评论，我们的网站 EnglishPod.com 随时开放

300
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,360
and ready for you.
欢迎你。

301
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:14,360
So thanks for downloading this lesson, you guys.
所以感谢你们下载这节课。

302
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,360
And until next time, goodbye.
下次再见，拜拜。

303
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:44,120
We'll see you guys out there.
我们外面见。
